us Tomalin)] ([https://web.archive.org/web/20161023133635/http://hplinguistics.pbworks.com/f/Tomalin%20Bloomfield%20maths.pdf archived version])\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110525040538/http://www.nmnh.si.edu/naa/fa/bloomfield.pdf  Finding Aid to the Papers of Leonard Bloomfield], National Anthropological Archives, Smithsonian Institution ([http://anthropology.si.edu/naa/fa/bloomfield.pdf archived version])\n* [http://www.linguisticsociety.org/about/who-we-are/lsa-awards#bloomfield Leonard Bloomfield Book Award, Linguistic Society of America]\n* [https://www.lib.uchicago.edu/e/scrc/findingaids/view.php?eadid=ICU.SPCL.BLOOMFIELD Guide to the Leonard Bloomfield Papers 1935-1943] at the [https://www.lib.uchicago.edu/scrc/ University of Chicago Special Collections Research Center ]\n\n{{Philosophy of language}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bloomfield, Leonard}}\n[[Category:1887 births]]\n[[Category:1949 deaths]]\n[[Category:American Jews]]\n[[Category:Linguists from the United States]]\n[[Category:Harvard College alumni]]\n[[Category:Leipzig University alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Chicago alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Wisconsin&ndash;Madison alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Cincinnati faculty]]\n[[Category:Ohio State University faculty]]\n[[Category:Yale University faculty]]\n[[Category:Phonologists]]\n[[Category:Morphologists]]\n[[Category:University of Chicago faculty]]\n[[Category:Linguists of Algic languages]]\n[[Category:American Sanskrit scholars]]\n[[Category:Linguistic Society of America presidents]]\n[[Category:People from Elkhart Lake, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:20th-century linguists]]\n", "name_user": "Edwardhessjr", "label": "safe", "comment": "Changed the nationality of this individual from \"Spanish\" to \"American\"", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leonard_Bloomfield"}
{"title_page": "2007 World Figure Skating Championships", "text_new": "{{Infobox Figure Skating Competition\n| title = 2007 World Figure Skating Championships\n| image = \n| imagesize = \n| caption = \n| comptype = ISU Championship\n| startdate = March 20\n| enddate = 25\n| skatingseason = 2006\u201307\n| location = [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]\n| host = \n| venue = [[Tokyo Metropolitan Gymnasium]]\n| prizemoney = US $710,000\n| championmen = {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Brian Joubert]]\n| championladies = {{flagicon|JPN}} [[Miki Ando]]\n| championpairs = {{flagicon|CHN}} [[Shen Xue]] / [[Zhao Hongbo]]\n| championdance = {{flagicon|BUL}} [[Albena Denkova]] / [[Maxim Staviski]]\n| previouscomp = [[2006 World Figure Skating Championships|2006 World Championships]]\n| nextcomp = [[2008 World Figure Skating Championships|2008 World Championships]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2007 [[World Figure Skating Championships]]''' was a senior international [[figure skating competition]] sanctioned by the [[International Skating Union]]. Medals were awarded in the disciplines of [[single skating|men's singles, ladies' singles]], [[pair skating]], and [[ice dancing]]. The event was held at the [[Tokyo Metropolitan Gymnasium]] in [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]] from March 20 to 25.\n\n==Competition notes==\nThe competition was open to skaters from [[International figure skating|ISU member nations]] who had reached the age of 15 by July 1, 2006. The corresponding competition for younger skaters was the [[2007 World Junior Figure Skating Championships|2007 World Junior Championships]].\n\nBased on the results of the [[2006 World Figure Skating Championships|2006 World Championships]], each country was allowed between one and three entries per discipline. National associations selected their entries based on their own criteria.\n\nDue to the large number of entries at the World Championships, only the top 24 single skaters and top 20 pairs advanced to the free skating after the short program. In ice dancing, the top 30 couples in the [[compulsory dance]] advanced to the [[original dance]], and the top 24 couples after the original dance advanced to the [[Free dance (figure skating)|free dance]].\n\n[[Yukari Nakano]] and [[Carolina Kostner]] tied for 5th place with 168.92 points overall. Nakano finished 5th place on the tiebreak (free skating placement) and Kostner ended 6th.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kaye|first=Rosaleen|title=2007 World Figure Skating Championships, Ladies' Free Skate Highlights|url=http://www.goldenskate.com/articles/2006/032507_ll.shtml |date=March 25, 2007|accessdate=March 4, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100112183207/http://www.goldenskate.com/articles/2006/032507_ll.shtml |archivedate=January 12, 2010 }}</ref> In the ladies' event, two world records were set: [[Yuna Kim]] for the short program with a score of 71.95,<ref>{{cite web|last=Kaye|first=Rosaleen|title=2007 World Figure Skating Championships, Ladies' Short Program Highlights|url=http://www.goldenskate.com/articles/2006/032507_ls.shtml |date=March 25, 2007|accessdate=March 4, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100112183212/http://www.goldenskate.com/articles/2006/032507_ls.shtml |archivedate=January 12, 2010 }}</ref> and [[Mao Asada]] for the free skating with a score of 133.13.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usfigureskating.org/event_story.asp?id=38073 |title=Welcome to U.S. Figure Skating |work=U.S. Figure Skating |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071213162440/http://usfigureskating.org/event_story.asp?id=38073 |archivedate=2007-12-13 }}</ref>\n\n[[Shen Xue]] / [[Zhao Hongbo]] from [[People's Republic of China|China]] set a new world record of 71.07 points under the [[ISU Judging System]] for pairs' short program.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/winter/2007-03-20-figure-skating-worlds_N.htm|title=Chinese pair dominates at figure skating worlds - USATODAY.com|work=USA Today}}</ref> Zhao proposed marriage to Shen on the ice following their free skating.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2010/SPORT/02/16/olympics.skating/index.html|title=Chinese couple cap comeback with figure skating gold|work=CNN}}</ref>\n\n==Medals table==\n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = \n | flag_template  = \n | event          = \n | team           = \n | gold_JPN = 1 | silver_JPN = 2 | bronze_JPN = 0\n | gold_CHN = 1 | silver_CHN = 1 | bronze_CHN = 0\n | gold_BUL = 1 | silver_BUL = 0 | bronze_BUL = 0\n | gold_FRA = 1 | silver_FRA = 0 | bronze_FRA = 0\n | gold_CAN = 0 | silver_CAN = 1 | bronze_CAN = 0\n | gold_GER = 0 | silver_GER = 0 | bronze_GER = 1\n | gold_KOR = 0 | silver_KOR = 0 | bronze_KOR = 1\n | gold_SUI = 0 | silver_SUI = 0 | bronze_SUI = 1\n | gold_USA = 0 | silver_USA = 0 | bronze_USA = 1\n}}\n\n==Results==\n===Men===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Name\n! Nation\n! Total points\n! colspan=\"2\" width=\"80px\" | [[Short program (figure skating)|SP]]\n! colspan=\"2\" width=\"80px\" | [[Free skating|FS]]\n|- bgcolor=\"gold\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''1'''\n| [[Brian Joubert]] || {{FRA}} ||240.85||1||83.64||3||157.21\n|- bgcolor=\"silver\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''2'''\n| [[Daisuke Takahashi]] || {{JPN}} ||237.95||3||74.51||1||163.44\n|- bgcolor=\"cc9966\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''3'''\n| [[St\u00e9phane Lambiel]] || {{SUI}} ||233.35||6||72.70||2||160.65\n|-\n! 4\n| [[Tom\u00e1\u0161 Verner]] || {{CZE}} ||226.25||9||70.45||4||155.80\n|-\n! 5\n| [[Evan Lysacek]] || {{USA}} ||222.18||5||73.49||5||148.69\n|-\n! 6\n| [[Jeffrey Buttle]] || {{CAN}} ||214.96||2||79.90||8||135.06\n|-\n! 7\n| [[Nobunari Oda]] || {{JPN}} ||209.94||14||67.17||6||142.77\n|-\n! 8\n| [[Johnny Weir]] || {{USA}} ||206.97||4||74.26||10||132.71\n|-\n! 9\n| [[Kristoffer Berntsson]] || {{SWE}} ||206.29||15||66.09||7||140.20\n|-\n! 10\n| [[Sergei Davydov (figure skater)|Sergei Davydov]] || {{BLR}} ||203.05||8||70.72||12||132.33\n|-\n! 11\n| [[Alban Pr\u00e9aubert]] || {{FRA}} ||202